? Martin Seligman's theory of learned helplessness, originally studied in animals, proposes that organisms stop trying to escape adverse conditions when they learn that what is true?
[A] The punishment is not severe enough to cause lasting harm
[B] Other members of their group are also unable to escape
[C] Their environment will eventually change on its own
[D]* Their actions have no effect on the outcome
